Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.890 --> 00:00:09.790
Your skin is the outer layer of protection
to your body. Exposure to some chemicals and

00:00:09.790 --> 00:00:14.619
other hazardous materials can lead to this
protection being broken down. It can cause

00:00:14.619 --> 00:00:19.890
pain, discomfort and long term ill health.

00:00:20.699 --> 00:00:24.480
So where do the risks come from?

00:00:24.480 --> 00:00:29.539
Your skin can come into contact with hazardous
materials through everyday work activities

00:00:29.539 --> 00:00:29.999
such as

00:00:29.999 --> 00:00:35.820
1. Wet work and use of chemicals in many workplaces
2. Mixing or decanting chemicals and materials

00:00:35.820 --> 00:00:42.820
3. Having skin contact with substances on
contaminated surfaces, containers or clothing

00:00:42.890 --> 00:00:45.449
or
4. Exposure to, or working with animals or

00:00:45.449 --> 00:00:52.449
food stuffs
