00:01:42.930 --> 00:01:45.759
So how does all this affect your health?

00:01:45.759 --> 00:01:48.560
Damage to your skin can lead to a number of
health effects:

00:01:48.560 --> 00:01:55.009
15. Irritant dermatitis or burns
16. Skin sensitisation and allergic dermatitis

00:01:55.009 --> 00:01:58.840
even to very small quantities
17. Pain and discomfort

00:01:58.840 --> 00:02:05.840
18. Infection
19. Sunburn and possibly Cancer

00:02:09.149 --> 00:02:11.020
How do you control the risks?

00:02:11.020 --> 00:02:15.870
Taking steps to control the risks means you
must identify which hazardous materials staff

00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:21.480
are exposed to. Then consider what steps are
needed to remove or reduce this exposure,

00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:22.090
for example:

00:02:22.090 --> 00:02:26.319
20. Use chemicals and hazardous substances
that are less harmful to skin

00:02:26.319 --> 00:02:30.180
21. Ensure good containment of the hazardous
material

00:02:30.180 --> 00:02:35.159
22. Consider tools and working practices that
would minimise exposure to wet work and chemicals

00:02:35.159 --> 00:02:39.209
23. Provide and maintain good work equipment
and extraction systems

00:02:39.209 --> 00:02:45.090
24. Provide suitable protective equipment
such as overalls, gloves or aprons as appropriate

00:02:45.090 --> 00:02:50.989
25. Practice good storage and house keeping
26. Consider skin health checks for exposed

00:02:50.989 --> 00:02:54.060
staff
27. Always monitor your systems to ensure

00:02:54.060 --> 00:02:55.980
they are working correctly

00:02:55.980 --> 00:03:00.920
Following these examples will help you reduce
your health risks at work. For more information,

